title: Secondary School Certificate (SSC)
result: GPA 5.0 with General Scholarship with average 92.6%
description:
During my school years, I excelled academically, earning top honors and numerous awards. I was the topper at my school, a testament to my hard work and perseverance. I received several scholarships, including those from The Students Welfare Foundation (2013-2016), The Scholars Forum (2015), Nur MD. Sir Memory Scholarship (2013), BICAL Foundation (2013), Bangladesh Cadet Academy (2011-2016), Hazi Shahbuddin Memory Scholarship (2014-2015), and BBKs.

In national essay competitions, I achieved 1st place at Ideal College (2018), International Customs Day (2017), and National Children Day (2017). I also earned 2nd place at the Bangladesh Association for the Aged and Institute of Geriatric Medicine (2016) and received an Honourable Mention from TIB. Additional accolades include 3rd place at National Power Week (2014), 2nd place at Nazrul Institute, and 1st place at Dhaka Imperial College (2014).

My achievements in talent hunts include being recognized as Dhaka Divisional Best Student in Language and Literature (2018) and Thana Best Student from 2014 to 2018. In Olympiads, I secured 1st place in Chemistry Olympiad and Extempore Speech at the DGBHS Inter School Science Festival (2017), 1st place in Extempore Speech at the 10th ISTARC Science and Technology Festival (2017), and 1st place in Nature Olympiad and Junior Science Olympiad (Regional) 2015. I also had the honor of receiving the Best Student Award in Language and Literature from the Honourable Prime Minister, which was a profound source of inspiration for me.

title: Higher Secondary Certificate (HSC)
description:
At Holy Cross College, I ranked among the top 3 students academically, demonstrating my commitment to excellence. I served as the Co-ordinating Secretary for the English Language Club in 2019, and actively participated in the Holy Cross College Science Club and Debating Club, which strengthened my critical thinking, communication, and teamwork skills.

My achievements include 4th place in the National Human Rights Essay Competition 2020 (Dhaka Division-1st) and 13th in the Eastern University Essay Competition. I also excelled in Olympiads and fairs, winning 1st place in the Earth Olympiad, 2nd in the Extempore Speech at the LCGHS Inter School and College Fair 2019, 3rd in the Math Olympiad, and 2nd in the Chemistry Olympiad at the Holy Cross College 17th Inter College Science Festival 2018. Additionally, I organized the 1st Inter College English Language Festival with HCCELC, enhancing my skills in writing, public speaking, scientific inquiry, and event organization. These experiences have been instrumental in preparing me for future challenges and opportunities.
